Doug BrydenPartner, Head of the Operational Risk Groupdouglas.bryden@traverssmith.com+ 44 (0)20 7295 3205

Doug is a partner in the Corporate Department and heads our Operational Risk Group, which specialises in UK, EU and international Environment, Regulatory and Product & Trade law.Doug's transactional, advisory and contentious practice focuses on a range of compliance and risk management issues, including:Environment, health and safety liabilitiesChemical and hazardous substances lawPermitting and operational complianceProduct safety, liability and recallsTrade controls and sanctionsAnti-bribery and corruptionBusiness ethics, human rights and corporate transparencyClimate change and energy efficiencyDoug has particular expertise in the energy, natural resources, healthcare and chemical sectors and is the current chair of our cross-departmental Healthcare & Pharmaceuticals Sector Group.Recent work includes advising:GDF Suez on regulatory, licencing and environmental issues on its entry into the UK's onshore unconventional (shale) gas market and subsequent project development supportNike, Inc. on UK and EU chemical law, product stewardship and brand managementMajor pharmaceutical supplier on compliance with UK and EU pharmaceutical controls and a potential regulatory notification and product recallBridgepoint on regulatory aspects of its purchase of Quotient Clinical, a clinical testing and development businessBosch Solar Energy on a large solar park in Trefullock, England and a number of other solar projectsPrivate equity houses such as Bridgepoint and The Carlyle Group on the application of the UK's CRC Energy Efficiency SchemePalletway (UK) Limited on defending a serious health and safety at work prosecution in the Crown CourtTrafigura Limited and Trafigura Beheer B.V. on their defence of the high profile personal injury claim involving c.30,000 claimants from the Ivory Coast. This long running dispute was one of the largest pieces of environmental litigation ever brought before a UK courtMitsubishi Rayon Co., Ltd, alongside Paul Weiss, on environmental and regulatory issues with its £1.6bn acquisition of the Lucite International chemicals businessAviva Investors on environment, social and governance (ESG) and related ethical investment issuesThe directories list Doug as one of the UK's leading environment and regulatory lawyers and note that he is "lauded for his intellectual strength, clear drive and passion" as well as being ''commercial'' with a "deep understanding of his field".In addition to being the General Editor of Commercial Environmental Law & Liability (Sweet & Maxwell), Doug has also lectured on Brighton University's Environmental Policy and Law MSc course and is an active member of the UK Environmental Law Association and City of London Law Society's Environment Committee.
















