Board of Directors
Roderick M. Bryden
Chairman, CEO, Plasco Energy Group Inc.
Owner, Chairman, SC Stormont Holdings Inc.
Mr. Rod Bryden is Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Plasco Energy Group Inc.  Plasco applies plasma arc technology to refine synthetic gas to produce natural gas equivalent fuel from various feed stocks, including Municipal Solid Waste.
Mr. Bryden is the majority owner and Chairman of SC Stormont Inc., which specializes in the leadership and development of small to mid-sized Canadian businesses. Mr. Bryden is also a Director and Chairman Clearford Water Systems Inc. a TSXV listed company.
Mr. Bryden began his career as Professor of Law at the University of Saskatchewan. Moving to Ottawa, he held positions with the Government of Canada before he co-founded and became President of Systemhouse Ltd in 1974.
He founded Paperboard Industries Corporation (PIC) in 1976 which by 1990 became Canada’s largest manufacturer of paper from recycled fibre and paperbox packaging.
In 1992, he became the principal owner of the Ottawa Senators Hockey Club, and The Palladium Corporation which, in 1996, opened the Corel Center, home of the Ottawa Senators. He sold the team and building in 2004.
Mr. Bryden founded SC Stormont Inc in 2004 and co-founded Plasco in 2005.
