Mr. C. Ian Ross has been Managing Partner of Killdeer Management since October 1990. He serves as Chairman of 6N Silicon Inc. Mr. Ross served as President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Provincial Papers Inc., and as President and Chief Executive Officer of Paperboard Industries Corporation. He has been Chairman of Working Ventures Canadian Fund Inc., since April 1999. He has been Chairman of Pet Valu Inc., since September 5, 2003. Mr. Ross is Chairman of GrowthWorks … WV Canadian Fund Inc.
Mr. Ross serves as Chairman of the Board of World Heart Corporation and has been its Director since February 22, 2000. Mr. Ross also serves as Director of Pet Valu Canada Inc. and Pet valu International Inc., subsidiaries of Pet Valu Inc. He serves as a Director of Working Ventures Canadian Fund Inc. He has been a Director of Comcare Health Services since February 1999 and Praeda Management Systems Inc., since February 1999. He has been a Director at Ontario Power Generation Inc., since December 2003.
Mr. Ross is Lead Director in the area of Finance for OPG. Mr. Ross serves as a Director of Walton Ontario Land 1 Corporation, the General Partner of Walton Ontario Land L.P. 1. Mr. Ross served as Senior Director of Administration in the Dean’s Office at the Richard Ivy School of Business, University of Western Ontario, since July 1999 until September 2003. He is a graduate of the University of Western Ontario, has a bachelor of laws degree from the University of Toronto and has been a member of the Law Society of Upper Canada since 1968.

Glenn Gold
Director, Clearford Industries Inc.
Glenn Gold is the founder and President of Lytton Financial Inc., a Toronto-based boutique investment banking firm active in raising capital, providing merger & acquisition advisory services and acting as placement agent for investment funds. Glenn is the former Executive Vice President and Managing Director, Head of Corporate Finance and Advisory (investment banking) at HSBC Securities (Canada) Inc. and Director and Co-Head of Investment Banking at Richardson Greenshields of Canada Limited. At these firms, Glenn served on their respective boards of directors, executive committees and liability/underwriting approvals committees. He has also served on the Board of Directors of HSBC Capital Canada Inc., a merchant bank, as well as other public and not-for-profit boards.
In over 25 years as an investment banker, Glenn has worked on a wide variety of financings and advisory assignments for large and small private and public companies involved in various industries.
Glenn earned a B.A. (Honours English, Cum Laude) from Concordia University and an M.B.A. from the University of Western Ontario.
 

 

 










































